defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Audiovisual
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A series of visual representations imparting an impression of motion when shown in succession. May or may not include sound. (e.g. films, video, etc.)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Collection
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: An aggregation of resources, which may encompass collections of one resourceType as well as those of mixed types. A collection is described as a group; its parts may also be separately described. (e.g. A collection of samples, or various files making up a report)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Data paper
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A factual and objective publication with a focused intent to identify and describe specific data, sets of data, or data collections to facilitate discoverability. (i.e. A data paper describes data provenance and methodologies used in the gathering, processing, organizing, and representing the data)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Dataset
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: Data encoded in a defined structure.

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Event
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A non-persistent, time-based occurrence. (i.e. Descriptive information and/or content that is the basis for discovery of the purpose, location, duration, and responsible agents associated with an event such as a webcast or convention)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Image
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A visual representation other than text. (e.g. Digitised or born digital images, drawings or photographs)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Interactive resource
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A resource requiring interaction from the user to be understood, executed, or experienced. (e.g. Training modules, files that require use of a viewer (e.g., Flash), or query/response portals)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Model
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: An abstract, conceptual, graphical, mathematical or visualization model that represents empirical objects, phenomena, or physical processes. (e.g. different aspects of languages or a molecular biology reaction chain)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Other
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: Use this type when your output type does not fall within one of the other categories.

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Physical object
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A physical object or substance. (e.g. Artifacts, specimens, material samples, and features-of-interest of any size. Note that digital representations of physical objects should use one of the other resourceTypeGeneral values.)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Service
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: An organized system of apparatus, appliances, staff, etc., for supplying some function(s) required by end users. (e.g. Data management service, or long-term preservation service)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Software
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A computer program other than a computational notebook, in either source code (text) or compiled form. Use this type for general software components supporting scholarly research. Use the “ComputationalNotebook” value for virtual notebooks.

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Sound
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A resource primarily intended to be heard. (e.g. an audio recording)

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Text
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A resource consisting primarily of words for reading that is not covered by any other textual resource type in this list.

defaultResearchOutputTypes.name: Workflow
defaultResearchOutputTypes.description: A structured series of steps which can be executed to produce a final outcome, allowing users a means to specify and enact their work in a more reproducible manner. (e.g. Computational workflows involving sequential operations made on data by wrapped software and may be specified in a format belonging to a workflow management system, such as Taverna)
